}^3$ are planes and\nspheres of parabolic type and that, in contrast to the $r$-connection, the\ncurvature tensor associated with the isotropic Levi-Civita connection vanishes\nidentically for $any$ pseudo-isotropic surface, as also happens in simply\nisotropic space.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 3 Jan 2018 21:43:27 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 30 Oct 2018 13:03:18 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 19 Mar 2019 10:26:13 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Fri, 31 May 2019 14:00:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-06-03"}
